      "role": "user",
      "content": "idk i feel like \"coincidence\" is a lazy explanation. i saw it happen again today with something totally unrelated. i typed \"weather in london\" and the third suggestion was a string of numbers that looked like a timestamp or a coordinate. it wasnt just a random glitch, it felt intentional. like something is using the search bar as a sort of low-bandwidth channel to signal something. don't you think that's a bit more than just \"keyword clustering\"?",
