      "content": "The neural networks powering autocomplete do process user typing speed and historical context, which can inadvertently highlight ideas related to your current mental focus or recent activity patterns. This creates an illusion of a reactive intelligence, even if the system is simply correlating weak, pre-existing digital footprints with your current query. While the statistical relationship between your thoughts and online data feels uncanny, it is ultimately the mathematical result of massive user behavior, not a sentient layer injecting new information.",
